2724:
title: WFP Haiti Market Price Monitoring, September 2024 
 content: Key Points
- A 5% increase in the cost of the food basket was observed at the national level, rising from 25.667 Gourdes in July to 26.865 Gourdes in August for a family of 5 . This variation is due to some shortages of wheat flour and rice, particularly in the communes of Anse d'Hainault, CapHaïtien, Jacmel, Saint Jean du Sud, Aquin, Pestel, Chardonnières and Anse à Galets;
- A significant increase in the cost of the food basket, reaching up to 16% in certain regions, in particular the Nord-Ouest (+16%) and the Sud (+14%);
- The cost of the food basket in certain departments, including Artibonite, Nord, Nord-Est and Sud-Est, remained stable or decreased by 0%, 5%, 4% and 3% respectively;
- At the national level, the average price of ground maize and vegetable oil remained stable, while the average price of sugar decreased slightly by 7%;
- Most food products are available in all markets, with the exception of wheat flour and rice in certain communes. Beans are becoming increasingly scarce in the departments.
